## Prohibited Content

- Real operational data.
- Raw source bulk copy.
- Sensitive requirement text.
- Runtime test code.
- C# source, solution, project, XAML, build assets, scripts, binaries, or executable packaging.
- PLC/device code.
- Live target write support or external mutation.
- GitHub Actions or cloud CI.
- IP, port, tag value, live parameter, secret, credential, private input, live config, or equipment detail.

## Approval Boundary

Synthetic fixture planning is design-only. Creating fixture files, tests, scripts, generated data, or runtime validation requires separate approval.

## Review Checklist

- Fixture categories are synthetic by construction.
- No real/private/live field is included.
- Source-use decisions are followed.
- No fixture file or runtime test is created.
- Prohibited content is absent.
- Acceptance evidence relationship is explicit.
